Market Analysis and Insights

Global Enteric Disease Testing-Treatment Market

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the enteric disease testing-treatment market to growing at a CAGR of 4.30% in the forecast period of 2022-2029. The market is expected to witness rapid expansion in terms of its capitalization as the major market players are focusing on development of products that help physicians and patients in a better healthcare delivery.

Enteric diseases are a type of intestinal disease caused by the presence of various microorganisms such as parasites, viruses, and bacteria. These microorganisms are commonly found in various food products and water bodies, and this disease category is also communicable between individuals. Enteric disease testing and treatment refer to the various diagnostic and therapeutic solutions offered by market participants to reduce or eliminate the impact of enteric diseases on the human body.

In the forecasted period, the increasing number of patients suffering from target diseases will be a significant driver of the growth of the enteric disease testing–treatment market. The availability of higher-quality products based on advanced technologies rather than traditional methods is also driving market growth. Furthermore, increased government intervention to improve people's living standards is expected to have a positive impact on the market. The government is primarily responsible for shifting the trend away from traditional diagnostic methods and toward advanced methods.

The market for enteric disease testing is hampered by high equipment and labour costs, as well as the mandatory requirement for sophisticated laboratory conditions for clinical diagnostics. These difficulties are expected to be overcome in the future as a result of the development of various advanced low-cost technologies such as enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) and polymerase chain reaction (PCR).

